1
00:00:00,209 --> 00:00:04,796
I need to know the truth
about Hijikata Toshizo...

2
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:09,092
He had the same look
in his eyes as you.

3
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:11,678
What's the fun
in doing the sensible thing?

4
00:00:11,762 --> 00:00:17,476
Doing what no one else
can is what makes you a badass.

5
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:19,686
[narrator] The time: the final
years of the Edo period.

6
00:00:21,647 --> 00:00:23,232
In a time of upheaval

7
00:00:23,273 --> 00:00:25,776
there were men who lived
fiercely and passionately

8
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:26,944
by the way of the sword.

9
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:29,905
To become...
the strongest man there is.

10
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:33,158
What a coincidence. Same here.

11
00:00:34,493 --> 00:00:35,953
[chuckles]

12
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:38,038
[Matsudaira]
I welcome you as the fools

13
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:41,166
who are ready to die
alongside the Aizu!

14
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:44,586
[narrator] Resisting
the relentless tide of history,

15
00:00:44,670 --> 00:00:46,046
they pressed on
with unwavering resolve.

16
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:50,342
[♪♪♪]

17
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:53,804
This is the story
of the last samurai

18
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:56,306
men who bloomed brilliantly

19
00:00:56,348 --> 00:01:00,310
in an age of turmoil,
and then fell.

20
00:01:00,394 --> 00:01:02,521
Let us bloom with all our might.

21
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:13,198
SONG OF THE SAMURAI

22
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:25,669
APRIL 1862, TOSA

23
00:01:25,711 --> 00:01:27,671
[indistinct chatter]

24
00:01:27,713 --> 00:01:30,299
[seabirds calling]

25
00:01:34,761 --> 00:01:36,847
Man, Edo is amazing!

26
00:01:36,888 --> 00:01:38,265
[all exclaiming]

27
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:40,017
It was packed with people,
and the food was delicious.

28
00:01:40,058 --> 00:01:44,354
And! And there were
a ton of strong fighters, too.

29
00:01:44,396 --> 00:01:48,942
But out of all of them, this guy
Toshi was the strongest.

30
00:01:49,026 --> 00:01:51,236
You just told us that story
about Toshi.

31
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:53,155
That's the fifth time.

32
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:56,908
Is that true, Ukichi?

33
00:01:56,992 --> 00:02:01,038
But still, Izo,
since it makes you laugh

34
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:03,540
I'd be happy to hear it
five or six times!

35
00:02:03,624 --> 00:02:04,833
Hey!

36
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,168
[all laughing]

37
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:10,589
Never mind all that.
Did you get a taste of this?

38
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:14,968
What? You eat pinky?

39
00:02:15,052 --> 00:02:17,054
You idiot! Edo has Yoshiwara,

40
00:02:17,095 --> 00:02:19,765
the land's greatest
pleasure district!

41
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:24,186
I'm talking about women!

42
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:29,066
[stammering]
I'm... not very good with women.

43
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:32,194
I've never seen or "tasted"
anything like that.

44
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:35,197
[all laughing]

45
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:41,286
Hey, Izo! Master Takechi
is calling for you!

46
00:02:43,622 --> 00:02:45,082
[thunder rumbling]

47
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:46,124
[Okada]
Assassination?

48
00:02:46,208 --> 00:02:47,709
[Oishi] Shh!

49
00:02:47,793 --> 00:02:49,628
Keep your voice down, Izo.

50
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:52,297
[Okada]
But still, an assassination...

51
00:02:53,674 --> 00:02:56,218
[Takechi]
It's divine retribution, Izo.

52
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:58,553
[Okada]
Divine retribution?

53
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:01,682
We are to eliminate
Yoshida Toyo.

54
00:03:04,226 --> 00:03:05,477
Who's that?

55
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:09,106
You don't even know who Toyo is?

56
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:10,941
He's the ringleader in Tosa

57
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:12,943
who oppresses
us lower-class samurai.

58
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:15,779
He sides with the shogunate's
plan to open the country

59
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:19,616
a vile man who is leading
our nation to ruin.

60
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:22,786
Izo.

61
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:26,540
You, too, are a member
of the Tosa Loyalist Party.

62
00:03:29,835 --> 00:03:32,254
Lend me your strength

63
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:35,424
so we may restore the Emperor
and expel the foreigners.

64
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:44,433
[thunder rumbling]

65
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:47,352
Mmm...

66
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:50,021
[inhales deeply]

67
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:55,736
No, I can't do that.
Anything but that.

68
00:03:55,819 --> 00:03:57,154
Izo!

69
00:03:57,195 --> 00:04:00,157
Izo! You'd really turn down
Master Takechi?

70
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:03,535
But...
I don't like killing people.

71
00:04:04,286 --> 00:04:05,579
I'm sorry.

72
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,082
Hey! Get back here, Izo!
Wait, Izo!

73
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:12,002
Let him go.
[Nasu] But, Master Takechi...

74
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:14,421
Well, wait and see.

75
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:18,550
[thunder rumbling]

76
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:25,015
[man sobbing]

77
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:26,767
[man]
Why would anyone do this?

78
00:04:30,061 --> 00:04:31,646
[sobbing]
Ukichi!

79
00:04:36,568 --> 00:04:37,736
Ukichi!

80
00:04:42,741 --> 00:04:44,201
Ukichi...

81
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:45,994
Ukichi...

82
00:04:46,036 --> 00:04:48,580
[Nasu] They were making
an example of Ukichi's father!

83
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,249
He petitioned the domain

84
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:53,210
to lessen the burden
of the labor tax.

85
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:55,420
[♪♪♪]

86
00:04:55,504 --> 00:04:57,422
And the one
who gave the order...

87
00:04:59,174 --> 00:05:00,592
it had to be Yoshida Toyo.

88
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:04,554
That damn Toyo!

89
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:07,724
How much more
will he make us suffer?

90
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:10,769
[♪♪♪]

91
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:42,467
Ukichi...

92
00:05:45,846 --> 00:05:46,972
Ukichi...

93
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:50,642
[sniffles]

94
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:03,071
I...

95
00:06:07,409 --> 00:06:08,994
will avenge...

96
00:06:12,956 --> 00:06:14,124
you.

97
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:20,964
I'm sorry, Ukichi.

98
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:25,594
I'm sorry, Izo.

99
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:49,159
[Oishi] Yoshida Toyo!
It's divine retribution!

100
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:03,048
You think a bunch
of Loyalist Party monkeys

101
00:07:04,883 --> 00:07:06,718
can take me down?

102
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:15,060
[Okada]
Why?

103
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:18,772
Why...

104
00:07:20,398 --> 00:07:22,567
Why did you kill Ukichi?

105
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:25,779
Another one, huh?

106
00:07:27,322 --> 00:07:28,531
Ukichi...

107
00:07:30,784 --> 00:07:34,371
looked up to me
like an older brother.

108
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:37,499
[Yoshida] What is this nonsense
you're spouting?

109
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,877
You die first!

110
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:41,962
[flesh rends]

111
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:45,048
[thunder booms]

112
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:50,887
Impossible...
that a lowly samurai...

113
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:56,810
could be this skilled...

114
00:07:56,893 --> 00:08:00,438
[♪♪♪]

115
00:08:00,522 --> 00:08:02,399
[Oishi] Izo!

116
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:03,900
[Nasu] You did it!

117
00:08:03,942 --> 00:08:07,362
It's divine retribution!
It's divine retribution!

118
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:08,363
You did it, Izo!

119
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:10,532
[Nasu &amp; Oishi celebrating]

120
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:20,792
And that was the beginning
of Izo the Manslayer.

121
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:28,967
After that, following
Takechi Hanpeita's orders

122
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,636
he cut down one key shogunate
official after another.

123
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:38,476
So he was
a completely different man

124
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:41,438
from when he met my grandfather,
Hijikata Toshizo.

125
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:46,651
A different man?
That's putting it mildly.

126
00:08:46,735 --> 00:08:47,610
Eh?

127
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:49,612
When a man with a kind soul

128
00:08:49,654 --> 00:08:52,407
is forced to keep killing
brutally...

129
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:55,660
Do you know what happens to him?

130
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,084
He shatters.

131
00:09:04,335 --> 00:09:05,879
Hold it!

132
00:09:05,962 --> 00:09:06,963
KYO, JULY 1863

133
00:09:07,839 --> 00:09:10,008
Surrender! Izo the Manslayer!

134
00:09:11,593 --> 00:09:12,844
Stay away.

135
00:09:15,013 --> 00:09:16,264
Don't come near.

136
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:17,307
[all yell fiercely]

137
00:09:18,183 --> 00:09:22,062
[♪♪♪]

138
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:29,736
[breathes deeply]

139
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:48,213
[wind whistling]

140
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:09,692
[baby crying]

141
00:10:23,706 --> 00:10:25,667
[man 1]
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

142
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,585
Hey, what's going on?

143
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:28,753
The Mibu Ronin are coming.

144
00:10:28,837 --> 00:10:30,547
The Mibu Roshigumi?

145
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:34,592
[man 1]
Check out that cocky bastard
strutting at the very front.

146
00:10:34,676 --> 00:10:37,554
Rumor is
he killed Tanaka Shinbei.

147
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:39,597
[man 2] Hijikata Toshizo,
the vice-commander?

148
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:40,890
[man 3]
Yep.

149
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:42,142
Toshizo?

150
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:47,772
Hey, they're coming.
Yeah.

151
00:11:16,426 --> 00:11:19,345
[♪♪♪]

152
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:23,183
[clattering]
[dog barking]

153
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:29,314
What's up Toshi?

154
00:11:30,732 --> 00:11:33,234
I feel like we're being watched.

155
00:11:33,318 --> 00:11:34,777
Huh?

156
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:36,321
A loyalist assassin?

157
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:40,825
No, it's probably nothing.

158
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:10,313
[narrator] By this time,
the Mibu Roshigumi had grown

159
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:13,858
and was split
into two major factions.

160
00:12:15,193 --> 00:12:18,363
The first was led by
Commander Kondo Isami...

161
00:12:18,446 --> 00:12:19,697
[Hijikata] One!

162
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:21,366
...with Vice-Commanders
Hijikata Toshizo

163
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:24,494
and Yamanami Keisuke,

164
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:27,747
the Shieikan faction.

165
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:30,667
[Hijikata] One, two!
[all] One, two!

166
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:35,088
One, two!
[all] One, two!

167
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:37,674
[narrator] The other
was the Serizawa faction,

168
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:40,343
led by First Commander
Serizawa Kamo

169
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:43,179
Vice-Commander Niimi Nishiki

170
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:49,435
and Assistant Vice-Commander
Hirayama Goro.

171
00:12:50,853 --> 00:12:53,648
[Todo] Don't tell me

172
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:57,360
they went out drinking again
last night

173
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:59,529
and still aren't back.

174
00:13:01,072 --> 00:13:04,784
[groaning]
Those bastards.

175
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:06,744
Incredible!

176
00:13:06,828 --> 00:13:08,830
Mr. Todo
sure is impressive!

177
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:10,999
How about that, Shimada?

178
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:15,670
SHIMADA KAI

179
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:17,714
Damn, Shimada!

180
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:18,923
You're a beast!
Like a god of war!

181
00:13:19,007 --> 00:13:23,177
Hey, Shimada!
Don't get cocky, rookie.

182
00:13:23,261 --> 00:13:25,805
I'm sorry.
I got a little carried away.

183
00:13:25,888 --> 00:13:28,891
Put those down, now!
Put those down!

184
00:13:28,975 --> 00:13:31,894
All of you,
drop and give me push-ups!

185
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:34,355
[Aridoshi]
Mr. Yamanami.

186
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:47,368
[Todo] 11, 12, 13
[all] 11, 12, 13

187
00:13:47,452 --> 00:13:51,956
[Todo] 14, 15, 16...
[all] 14, 15, 16...

188
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:57,128
[sighs]

189
00:14:00,423 --> 00:14:02,508
You want to switch
to the other faction?

190
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:06,554
Tell me why.

191
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:11,392
I wish to train
under Master Serizawa.

192
00:14:11,434 --> 00:14:15,813
They see more action,
and they're flush with cash.

193
00:14:15,897 --> 00:14:19,776
Plus, it's fun. They get
to party almost every night.

194
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:21,402
[all] Exactly.

195
00:14:22,904 --> 00:14:24,322
So that's the real reason, huh?

196
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:27,075
[students stammering]

197
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:29,118
[laughing]

198
00:14:31,496 --> 00:14:32,997
Well, yeah.
That makes sense.

199
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:36,084
[sighs]

200
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:37,335
Fine.

201
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:39,629
Do whatever you want.

202
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:42,298
Huh? Are you serious?

203
00:14:42,382 --> 00:14:44,217
Yeah. But...

204
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:47,178
on one condition.

205
00:14:48,971 --> 00:14:50,556
[Saito]
Wake up, Gen!

206
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:53,518
It's starting again!

207
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:57,063
[♪♪♪]

208
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:58,272
Yes.

209
00:14:59,524 --> 00:15:03,861
Well, well, look who's all here.

210
00:15:03,945 --> 00:15:05,988
Hey. It hasn't started yet,
right?

211
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:08,116
It starts now.

212
00:15:08,199 --> 00:15:09,826
Hey

213
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:11,244
come at me at once.

214
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:15,498
If you can land
just one strike on me

215
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:18,501
you can go to Serizawa's group
or wherever the hell you want.

216
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:19,669
Awesome.

217
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:21,337
Not confident, even four-on-one?

218
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:22,422
If you're that pathetic,

219
00:15:22,505 --> 00:15:24,173
they won't give you
the time of day.

220
00:15:26,843 --> 00:15:29,971
Hijikata,
mind if we add three more?

221
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,931
Yeah. I don't care.

222
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:33,182
That's seven men!

223
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:35,351
But even for Mr. Hijikata,
that's...

224
00:15:35,393 --> 00:15:37,019
Oi.

225
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:40,106
Hey.

226
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:43,901
On guard!
C'mon, take it seriously!

227
00:15:43,985 --> 00:15:45,903
What are you, scared? Hey!

228
00:15:45,987 --> 00:15:47,613
There are seven of us!
We can win this!

229
00:15:47,697 --> 00:15:48,614
Yeah!

230
00:15:48,698 --> 00:15:50,408
Good luck.
Yeah.

231
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:53,035
[students shouting]

232
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:56,080
Get him! Get him!

233
00:16:03,546 --> 00:16:06,299
What's the matter? Bring it!

234
00:16:11,053 --> 00:16:13,055
[students coughs]

235
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:14,098
Hey.

236
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:17,268
So, I take it
you're all staying?

237
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:22,398
Whoa! Look at you go, Toshi!

238
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:28,696
That was pathetic, you guys.
Gen.

239
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:30,281
Mm.

240
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:31,324
What is this?

241
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:33,159
Eh!

242
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:34,076
Hey!

243
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:35,495
I'll assist you.

244
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:40,124
So it's against you two?

245
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:45,379
Now this is getting interesting.

246
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:51,260
[♪♪♪]

247
00:16:58,309 --> 00:17:00,019
[laughs]

248
00:17:14,325 --> 00:17:16,244
[exclaiming]

249
00:17:16,327 --> 00:17:17,119
Dammit!

250
00:17:17,203 --> 00:17:18,538
Hey, it's not a lethal blow.

251
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:20,081
Awesome!

252
00:17:20,164 --> 00:17:22,416
Damn. He got me!

253
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:25,086
[Nagakura]
Man, what were you thinking?

254
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:28,339
What's the matter? You that
pissed off you lost to me?

255
00:17:28,422 --> 00:17:32,760
That's not it! You won the fight
against those guys, didn't you?

256
00:17:32,843 --> 00:17:34,971
Then why did you
run them all off?

257
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:36,222
If they want to leave,

258
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:37,723
there's no use
trying to stop them.

259
00:17:37,807 --> 00:17:39,100
[laughing]

260
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:40,643
That's so like you, Toshi.

261
00:17:40,685 --> 00:17:43,312
There you go again,
being so nonchalant.

262
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:47,149
Do you know how many men
we've lost to them this month?

263
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:49,151
Pardon the intrusion.
Huh?

264
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,365
You must all be tired.
Please, help yourselves.

265
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:56,117
Perfect timing.

266
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,494
You're always so thoughtful,
Aijiro.

267
00:17:58,578 --> 00:17:59,495
Not at all.

268
00:17:59,579 --> 00:18:00,496
SASAKI AIJIRO

269
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:02,873
I'm honored you
remembered my name, sir.

270
00:18:02,957 --> 00:18:06,168
What are you so tense about?

271
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:10,089
He's never this well-behaved
around me.

272
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:13,634
Even in the last practice,
he mercilessly beat me down.

273
00:18:13,718 --> 00:18:15,011
That's not right.

274
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:17,179
The one always beating me down
is you, Master!

275
00:18:17,263 --> 00:18:19,515
See? He's usually got
a much bigger mouth on him.

276
00:18:19,557 --> 00:18:22,852
What's this? Bragging about
your cute little disciple?

277
00:18:22,893 --> 00:18:24,312
[laughter]

278
00:18:27,565 --> 00:18:29,984
[sighing]

279
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,193
But...

280
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:33,154
is this really okay...

281
00:18:34,405 --> 00:18:37,283
for someone like me,
the son of a craftsman

282
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:39,702
to join the Mibu Roshigumi?

283
00:18:42,204 --> 00:18:44,206
If you can't join our ranks,

284
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:46,542
then we'd all have to quit
on the spot.

285
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:48,878
Right, Toshi?

286
00:18:48,919 --> 00:18:50,379
Huh.

287
00:18:50,421 --> 00:18:52,923
We're just farm boys ourselves.

288
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:54,216
[gasps]

289
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:55,593
[Kondo]
Aijiro...

290
00:18:56,927 --> 00:18:58,804
being a samurai isn't about
your social status...

291
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:01,557
It's about what's in here.

292
00:19:06,187 --> 00:19:08,939
Commander Kondo... Everyone...

293
00:19:09,023 --> 00:19:11,525
I swear, I absolutely swear...

294
00:19:11,609 --> 00:19:14,820
I will prove my worth
to all of you!

295
00:19:14,904 --> 00:19:17,281
Good. See that you do, Kojiro.

296
00:19:17,365 --> 00:19:19,492
It's Aijiro.
[Hijikata] Yeah, I know.

297
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:21,911
Thank you.

298
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:24,914
[slow clapping]

299
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:28,167
[Saeki]
Man, that's something else..

300
00:19:30,211 --> 00:19:33,422
That master-disciple bond,
you know?

301
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:37,259
It gets you right here.
Seriously, I'm so damn jealous.

302
00:19:37,301 --> 00:19:39,136
I want one of those too.

303
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:40,763
What the hell do you want?

304
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,516
Hey, Saeki!

305
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:45,976
What are you doing
skulking around here?

306
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:47,520
What about your patrol?

307
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:49,605
You're supposed to be
on duty today!

308
00:19:49,647 --> 00:19:50,773
SAEKI MATASABURO

309
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:52,483
Oh, that's right.

310
00:19:54,235 --> 00:19:56,946
Heard he was out again
last night.

311
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:59,657
You know, what's-his-name.

312
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:03,327
[laughing]
What was it again? Uzo? Muzo?

313
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:09,709
Izo! That's it, Izo. Okada Izo.

314
00:20:09,792 --> 00:20:11,419
[♪♪♪]

315
00:20:11,502 --> 00:20:14,380
He was prowling
Tominokoji last night.

316
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:16,632
Tominokoji?

317
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,637
You can just leave him to me.

318
00:20:21,721 --> 00:20:24,432
If you don't dispose of thugs
like him quickly

319
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:27,226
a man can't enjoy his sake
in peace.

320
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:29,562
Are you trying
to pick a fight?

321
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:32,314
[Saeki]
What's that supposed to mean?

322
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:34,567
Okada Izo is a manslayer,
you know.

323
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:40,406
Or was he a "friend" of yours,
Vice-Commander?

324
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:42,199
In fact, isn't protecting him

325
00:20:42,283 --> 00:20:45,411
the same as picking a fight
with our Aizu patrons?

326
00:20:47,413 --> 00:20:49,790
Saeki's not wrong
about any of this.

327
00:20:49,874 --> 00:20:51,250
This isn't right, Toshi.

328
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:52,543
[Kondo] Saeki,

329
00:20:53,461 --> 00:20:55,421
I apologize for this trouble.

330
00:20:57,006 --> 00:21:00,384
But Toshi would never do
anything to endanger the corps.

331
00:21:00,468 --> 00:21:01,969
You can rest assured of that.

332
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:09,310
I need you to give it your all
as a Vice-Commander's Assistant.

333
00:21:12,313 --> 00:21:13,856
Yes, sir. If that's an order
from the Commander,

334
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:15,149
I can't very well refuse.

335
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:16,942
Well then,
I'll be off on my patrol.

336
00:21:31,248 --> 00:21:34,877
Boss!
Why is he the same rank as me?

337
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:35,961
Settle down.

338
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:40,341
Saeki's attitude is certainly
nothing to be proud of.

339
00:21:40,424 --> 00:21:43,469
But you've noticed it as well,
I'm sure.

340
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:47,723
His killing intent
is not to be taken lightly.

341
00:21:47,807 --> 00:21:50,351
We'll likely see more men
of his ilk

342
00:21:50,434 --> 00:21:52,186
joining our ranks from now on.

343
00:21:52,269 --> 00:21:55,564
Yeah, we're getting more and
more guys with unknown pasts.

344
00:21:55,606 --> 00:21:59,485
It's getting more and more
difficult to maintain control.

345
00:22:02,446 --> 00:22:04,824
We may need to take
some new measures.

346
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:13,707
[indistinct chatter, singing]

347
00:22:35,479 --> 00:22:37,314
Looks like the master
of this place

348
00:22:37,398 --> 00:22:39,483
has agreed to our "donation."

349
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:40,693
Oh.

350
00:22:53,289 --> 00:22:54,582
Come on, have a drink.

351
00:22:54,665 --> 00:22:59,461
Master Serizawa.
You should train us sometime.

352
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:01,630
It's always booze and women
with you...

353
00:23:01,714 --> 00:23:03,757
our enemies
will walk all over us.

354
00:23:07,177 --> 00:23:10,389
Oume, go ahead and train him.

355
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:13,392
Me? Are you sure?
Yeah.

356
00:23:13,475 --> 00:23:14,393
[chuckles]

357
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:15,853
Are you...

358
00:23:17,354 --> 00:23:19,440
really that strong?

359
00:23:19,523 --> 00:23:21,525
You're always
drunk off your ass.

360
00:23:22,526 --> 00:23:24,278
I bet even I could take you.

361
00:23:24,361 --> 00:23:25,988
[Serizawa grumbles]

362
00:23:26,071 --> 00:23:27,448
I may not look it,

363
00:23:27,489 --> 00:23:30,951
but I've cut down
a Hokushin Itto-ryu master, too.

364
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:32,536
[sighing]

365
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:34,872
Is that right? Heh.

366
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:39,168
All right, I like your nerve.
I'll give you a lesson.

367
00:23:39,209 --> 00:23:40,794
Mm.
Huh?

368
00:23:42,504 --> 00:23:45,591
Try and kill me. Right now.

369
00:23:45,674 --> 00:23:46,800
[sniffs]

370
00:23:46,842 --> 00:23:48,052
Hell, if anything

371
00:23:49,219 --> 00:23:51,221
I'll even fight you bare-handed.

372
00:23:53,599 --> 00:23:55,851
I'm the chief commander
of the Mibu Ronin.

373
00:23:55,935 --> 00:23:58,520
If you take me down,
you'll be famous overnight.

374
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:01,857
The Imperialists
might pay you a fortune.

375
00:24:01,941 --> 00:24:03,817
Or perhaps... Ahem.

376
00:24:07,154 --> 00:24:11,408
Are you afraid of me,
even when I'm unarmed?

377
00:24:11,492 --> 00:24:13,077
[chuckling]

378
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:20,751
Don't you mock me.

379
00:24:25,798 --> 00:24:26,924
Come on.

380
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:29,551
[cries out]

381
00:24:29,635 --> 00:24:32,471
[gasping, exclaiming]

382
00:24:32,554 --> 00:24:36,475
Hey, do you all get it now?
This is how I train.

383
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:39,645
Come try to kill me
whenever you want. Got it?

384
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:42,106
[women scream]

385
00:24:44,650 --> 00:24:47,486
I'll follow your lead, Serizawa.

386
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:49,863
Pour it over my hand.

387
00:24:53,117 --> 00:24:56,120
[insects chirring]

388
00:24:56,203 --> 00:24:59,123
[♪♪♪]

389
00:25:04,503 --> 00:25:07,631
[Okada]
You're pretty damn good.

390
00:25:07,715 --> 00:25:10,050
[Hijikata] You've got
some skills yourself.

391
00:25:12,428 --> 00:25:15,597
We'll have another match,
Toshizo.

392
00:25:15,681 --> 00:25:17,224
[Hijikata]
Sure.

393
00:25:23,647 --> 00:25:27,693
[doshin]
You. What are you doing here?

394
00:25:34,867 --> 00:25:36,076
You're...

395
00:25:37,786 --> 00:25:39,288
Okada Izo.

396
00:25:39,371 --> 00:25:40,581
Izo?

397
00:25:44,668 --> 00:25:46,211
Don't come...

398
00:25:49,423 --> 00:25:50,841
You mustn't come.

399
00:25:54,553 --> 00:25:55,846
Don't come.

400
00:25:59,224 --> 00:26:00,851
You mustn't come.

401
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:06,940
[shudders]

402
00:26:12,571 --> 00:26:14,031
Again...

403
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:24,875
A man-slayer...

404
00:26:26,668 --> 00:26:28,378
[voice breaking]
A man-slayer like me...

405
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:30,881
[sniffles]

406
00:26:33,425 --> 00:26:34,760
has no right...

407
00:26:38,263 --> 00:26:39,890
to show up

408
00:26:41,058 --> 00:26:42,184
before Toshizo.

409
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:45,395
[sobbing]

410
00:26:56,990 --> 00:27:00,119
[man speaking indistinctly]

411
00:27:01,578 --> 00:27:03,664
I guess it was after
you all passed by

412
00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:07,042
he was rummaging through scraps
and other trash to eat.

413
00:27:07,084 --> 00:27:08,585
Eating... garbage?

414
00:27:08,669 --> 00:27:13,632
Yeah.
It was a ghastly sight to see.

415
00:27:19,805 --> 00:27:21,849
It was right here.

416
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:53,088
Will you let me know
if you see him again?

417
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:58,886
Before the magistrate's office.

418
00:28:01,013 --> 00:28:02,264
Got it?

419
00:28:02,306 --> 00:28:04,141
Understood.

420
00:28:07,811 --> 00:28:09,271
[man]
It's the man-slayer again!

421
00:28:09,313 --> 00:28:12,983
Move out of my way!

422
00:28:17,863 --> 00:28:19,698
[magistrate]
Hey, go on home now!

423
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:21,200
[onlooker]
What happened?

424
00:28:23,827 --> 00:28:25,454
[magistrate]
Go home now.

425
00:28:27,080 --> 00:28:28,290
Go home!

426
00:28:28,373 --> 00:28:30,918
[indistinct chatter]

427
00:28:37,841 --> 00:28:39,176
[Kondo]
Toshi.

428
00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:51,021
They both went down
with a single strike.

429
00:28:52,814 --> 00:28:55,275
As far as I know,
there's only one person

430
00:28:56,818 --> 00:28:58,320
capable of a feat
like this...

431
00:29:01,156 --> 00:29:02,282
It's Izo.

432
00:29:05,911 --> 00:29:07,913
I have to find him, and fast.

433
00:29:08,956 --> 00:29:10,999
Do you have any leads?

434
00:29:11,041 --> 00:29:12,501
No.

435
00:29:12,542 --> 00:29:14,169
But he has to be close.

436
00:29:16,546 --> 00:29:18,257
What will you do
when you find him?

437
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:27,975
Cut him down.

438
00:29:32,896 --> 00:29:34,481
Are you really sure about that?

439
00:29:36,984 --> 00:29:39,695
If you fight Izo
with a heartless blade,

440
00:29:39,778 --> 00:29:41,905
you'll be no different
than a man-slayer.

441
00:29:41,989 --> 00:29:44,700
If I don't do this now,
more people will die.

442
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:46,493
That won't do for you two.

443
00:29:49,788 --> 00:29:51,123
That won't do!

444
00:29:58,005 --> 00:30:02,009
Did you two meet just to kill?

445
00:30:04,136 --> 00:30:05,262
Remember...

446
00:30:07,931 --> 00:30:10,058
why you aimed
to be the strongest.

447
00:30:14,771 --> 00:30:16,148
You two were...

448
00:30:21,153 --> 00:30:22,237
Friends...

449
00:30:24,114 --> 00:30:24,906
Right?

450
00:30:24,990 --> 00:30:28,118
[♪♪♪]

451
00:30:30,954 --> 00:30:32,456
Before I'm his friend...

452
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:36,835
I'm the vice-commander
of the Mibu Roshigumi.

453
00:30:53,143 --> 00:30:54,144
Izo...

454
00:30:58,315 --> 00:31:00,400
[bird cawing]

455
00:31:26,676 --> 00:31:28,095
I've been looking for you.

456
00:31:29,262 --> 00:31:30,305
Izo.

457
00:31:44,319 --> 00:31:45,487
Toshizo.

458
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:51,201
Hey.

459
00:31:54,996 --> 00:31:56,456
It's been a while.

460
00:32:02,421 --> 00:32:03,547
Toshizo.

461
00:32:10,387 --> 00:32:11,430
What is it?

462
00:32:16,518 --> 00:32:17,561
I'm...

463
00:32:20,439 --> 00:32:21,606
I'm...

464
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:27,737
As I kept cutting people
on command...

465
00:32:30,073 --> 00:32:31,408
And the men I fought

466
00:32:33,952 --> 00:32:35,745
started to look like scarecrows.

467
00:32:39,332 --> 00:32:40,417
Now...

468
00:32:42,210 --> 00:32:44,296
I feel nothing
when I cut them down.

469
00:32:50,719 --> 00:32:52,721
So you've lost your heart?

470
00:33:06,860 --> 00:33:08,278
Honestly...

471
00:33:14,743 --> 00:33:16,620
I didn't want to meet you
like this.

472
00:33:18,288 --> 00:33:19,289
Don't.

473
00:33:23,710 --> 00:33:25,462
Guess we have no choice, Izo.

474
00:33:26,505 --> 00:33:28,131
Don't, Toshizo.

475
00:33:31,593 --> 00:33:34,012
At least I'll be the one
to cut you down...

476
00:33:38,642 --> 00:33:40,435
Vice-Commander, Mibu Roshigumi

477
00:33:42,145 --> 00:33:43,480
Hijikata Toshizo.

478
00:33:45,941 --> 00:33:47,317
Here I come!

479
00:33:51,154 --> 00:33:53,823
[♪♪♪]

480
00:33:57,118 --> 00:34:01,081
I am... Izo the Manslayer!

481
00:34:01,164 --> 00:34:03,291
No, you aren't.

482
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:12,509
[both grunting]

483
00:34:30,151 --> 00:34:31,861
Damn... you're strong.

484
00:34:34,531 --> 00:34:35,865
Interesting.

485
00:34:35,949 --> 00:34:37,576
[panting]

486
00:34:39,035 --> 00:34:41,079
You're still Izo,
through and through.

487
00:34:51,047 --> 00:34:52,465
From here on,

488
00:34:53,883 --> 00:34:55,802
I'm just... Hijikata Toshizo.

489
00:35:01,766 --> 00:35:04,019
You said it yourself, Izo.

490
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:05,854
"With wooden swords,
we could fight

491
00:35:05,895 --> 00:35:07,230
as many times as we wanted."

492
00:35:07,314 --> 00:35:09,316
But I guess that's not
an option now.

493
00:35:13,361 --> 00:35:17,741
This is a fight to the death.
Our first and our last duel.

494
00:35:24,331 --> 00:35:28,501
Izo... after this,
we can never do this again.

495
00:35:28,585 --> 00:35:31,421
There's no greater honor
than to fall by your blade.

496
00:35:32,339 --> 00:35:35,592
I know you feel the same. Izo!

497
00:35:38,053 --> 00:35:39,638
[yells fiercely]

498
00:35:47,562 --> 00:35:48,897
[cries out]

499
00:35:52,275 --> 00:35:54,611
Damn, that hurts!

500
00:35:54,694 --> 00:35:57,197
Hey! How's that feel?
Tell me, does a scarecrow bleed?

501
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,740
[both panting]

502
00:35:58,823 --> 00:36:01,826
What you just cut
wasn't a scarecrow, was it?

503
00:36:01,910 --> 00:36:05,497
See? You feel pain, don't you?

504
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:10,919
And the man I'm fighting
isn't a scarecrow either.

505
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:15,632
I'm fighting you! Okada Izo!

506
00:36:19,260 --> 00:36:21,513
[both groaning]

507
00:36:27,727 --> 00:36:31,731
Hey... What was it
we were striving for,

508
00:36:33,566 --> 00:36:34,484
Izo?

509
00:36:45,995 --> 00:36:52,293
[♪♪♪]

510
00:36:52,377 --> 00:36:55,505
To become the strongest man
alive, wasn't it?

511
00:37:03,179 --> 00:37:04,723
[exhales sharply]

512
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:08,351
[sighs]

513
00:37:33,501 --> 00:37:35,879
I don't need something like this

514
00:37:38,465 --> 00:37:40,467
to duel Toshizo...

515
00:37:41,718 --> 00:37:42,969
[sword clatters]

516
00:37:45,889 --> 00:37:47,640
[chuckling softly]

517
00:37:53,229 --> 00:37:54,898
[laughs]

518
00:37:56,024 --> 00:37:57,525
[sword clatters]

519
00:38:01,112 --> 00:38:04,657
That's more like it, Izo.

520
00:38:09,788 --> 00:38:11,289
Alright.

521
00:38:15,418 --> 00:38:16,586
You can continue...

522
00:38:18,129 --> 00:38:19,631
to fight with those.

523
00:38:19,714 --> 00:38:23,051
[♪♪♪]

524
00:38:26,763 --> 00:38:27,764
Boss...

525
00:38:40,860 --> 00:38:42,779
[laughing]

526
00:38:51,287 --> 00:38:52,622
Toshizo,

527
00:38:54,707 --> 00:38:55,834
bring it on!

528
00:38:59,754 --> 00:39:00,880
Yeah!

529
00:39:07,262 --> 00:39:08,888
[exhales fiercely]

530
00:39:14,811 --> 00:39:17,814
[both yell fiercely]

531
00:39:20,942 --> 00:39:24,487
[♪♪♪]

532
00:40:06,070 --> 00:40:07,655
I am Okada Izo!

533
00:40:07,697 --> 00:40:13,411
The strongest man in all Japan!

534
00:40:14,704 --> 00:40:19,167
I'm the greatest samurai
in all of Japan!

535
00:40:19,208 --> 00:40:20,460
[both grunt]

536
00:40:23,212 --> 00:40:25,673
[both panting]

537
00:40:30,845 --> 00:40:33,222
I won!

538
00:40:36,976 --> 00:40:39,687
[laughing heartily]

539
00:40:44,692 --> 00:40:46,694
Looks like another draw.

540
00:40:47,820 --> 00:40:48,863
Toshizo...

541
00:40:52,784 --> 00:40:54,035
Man...

542
00:40:56,579 --> 00:40:58,831
that was a damn good time.

543
00:40:58,915 --> 00:41:01,209
[laughing]

544
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:03,169
[groans]

545
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:19,686
Hey... Toshizo... Someday...

546
00:41:21,145 --> 00:41:22,480
Someday...

547
00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:27,777
we'll do this again.

548
00:41:30,655 --> 00:41:32,740
No matter how much
I boast of my strength,

549
00:41:32,782 --> 00:41:34,742
don't you dare
run away next time.

550
00:41:41,749 --> 00:41:43,001
[sobs]

551
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,088
Huh?

552
00:41:47,130 --> 00:41:49,716
[chuckles]

553
00:41:49,799 --> 00:41:51,843
What's wrong with you,
Toshizo?

554
00:41:53,594 --> 00:41:54,971
You're one to talk.

555
00:41:57,724 --> 00:42:02,186
No matter where you hide,
no matter where you run

556
00:42:03,521 --> 00:42:08,026
I'll find you
and beat the hell out of you.

557
00:42:09,694 --> 00:42:12,155
[chuckles, stammers]

558
00:42:15,158 --> 00:42:16,993
Toshizo...

559
00:42:17,076 --> 00:42:21,122
You're a real weirdo.

560
00:42:22,707 --> 00:42:26,127
We just made
this incredible promise...

561
00:42:26,210 --> 00:42:28,796
So why are you crying?

562
00:42:30,048 --> 00:42:31,674
Shut up!

563
00:42:33,301 --> 00:42:35,636
You're the one who's crying!

564
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:36,846
Huh?

565
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:39,015
What?

566
00:42:40,349 --> 00:42:41,768
But why...?

567
00:42:41,851 --> 00:42:46,355
[both laughing and crying]

568
00:42:54,113 --> 00:42:55,573
It's a promise, then.

569
00:43:00,912 --> 00:43:01,913
I promise.

570
00:43:07,043 --> 00:43:09,045
[laughing]

571
00:43:18,429 --> 00:43:20,181
[bell tinkling]

572
00:43:20,264 --> 00:43:23,226
[♪♪♪]

573
00:43:26,729 --> 00:43:30,691
[narrator] After that,
Okada Izo was captured in Kyo

574
00:43:30,775 --> 00:43:32,985
and extradited
to the Tosa Domain.

575
00:43:34,612 --> 00:43:36,739
He was imprisoned
with Takechi Hanpeita

576
00:43:36,823 --> 00:43:40,827
and the rest
of the Tosa Loyalist Party.

577
00:43:44,372 --> 00:43:45,414
[Okada]
Hey...

578
00:43:47,583 --> 00:43:49,127
You...

579
00:43:49,210 --> 00:43:50,628
[guard]
Huh?

580
00:43:51,838 --> 00:43:53,881
A wooden sword...

581
00:43:54,882 --> 00:43:56,884
Can you lend it to me?

582
00:44:00,096 --> 00:44:01,514
A wooden sword?

583
00:44:01,597 --> 00:44:02,640
[scoffs]

584
00:44:02,723 --> 00:44:04,934
What are you gonna do with that?

585
00:44:07,436 --> 00:44:08,938
Toshizo's...

586
00:44:10,439 --> 00:44:11,941
waiting for me.

587
00:44:19,448 --> 00:44:20,992
Toshizo...

588
00:44:22,535 --> 00:44:24,036
is getting stronger...

589
00:44:24,954 --> 00:44:26,122
[chuckles]

590
00:44:26,956 --> 00:44:28,708
...and waiting for me.

591
00:44:28,791 --> 00:44:32,920
[♪♪♪]

592
00:44:58,487 --> 00:45:00,740
Yah!
Tah! Tah!

593
00:45:03,618 --> 00:45:05,453
[chuckles]

594
00:45:05,494 --> 00:45:07,955
[narrator]
Then, on July 3, 1865...

595
00:45:08,039 --> 00:45:14,212
Okada Izo
was executed by beheading.

596
00:45:14,295 --> 00:45:16,964
They say he was swinging
that wooden sword

597
00:45:17,048 --> 00:45:19,175
right up to his final moment.

598
00:45:24,347 --> 00:45:25,473
[grunts fiercely]

599
00:45:28,851 --> 00:45:30,853
I can't believe it.

600
00:45:30,937 --> 00:45:33,314
The man they called
"Izo the Manslayer"...

601
00:45:34,857 --> 00:45:37,568
Once in Edo, and once in Kyo.

602
00:45:37,652 --> 00:45:42,448
To think that's all it took
to forge such a powerful bond.

603
00:45:45,076 --> 00:45:46,994
That's what it means
to cross swords

604
00:45:47,036 --> 00:45:49,330
with your life
on the line.

605
00:45:49,372 --> 00:45:52,917
Social status and personal
beliefs don't matter.

606
00:45:54,126 --> 00:45:58,297
You just throw your pure
strength at one another.

607
00:46:00,341 --> 00:46:04,428
A battle like that
is every samurai's dream.

608
00:46:06,555 --> 00:46:09,725
I'm envious of a bond like that.

609
00:46:09,809 --> 00:46:11,394
It may have been the last dream

610
00:46:12,770 --> 00:46:15,273
either of them ever had.

611
00:46:17,400 --> 00:46:19,068
Their last dream?

612
00:46:19,151 --> 00:46:20,111
Ah...

613
00:46:22,196 --> 00:46:23,489
Sadly...

614
00:46:25,032 --> 00:46:27,785
After that,
the battles we fought...

615
00:46:29,704 --> 00:46:33,082
were a far cry
from any such dream.

616
00:46:41,299 --> 00:46:44,635
Hey, Hijikata,
what are you doing?

617
00:46:44,719 --> 00:46:46,721
The corps regulations.

618
00:46:46,804 --> 00:46:49,265
To keep the riffraff in line.

619
00:46:50,099 --> 00:46:51,475
Eh?

620
00:47:01,652 --> 00:47:02,737
Mm.

621
00:47:02,778 --> 00:47:05,072
How very Toshi. I love it.

622
00:47:05,114 --> 00:47:06,490
You really think so?
Yeah.

623
00:47:08,117 --> 00:47:09,952
We'll fight and clash to keep
the corps' rules in place...

624
00:47:10,036 --> 00:47:11,746
and make sure
everyone stays in line.

625
00:47:11,829 --> 00:47:13,372
"Fight's on!"

626
00:47:16,834 --> 00:47:19,712
Aah!
You didn't have
to tear them, Soji!

627
00:47:19,754 --> 00:47:21,589
I'm impressed you
wrote something so idiotic.

628
00:47:21,630 --> 00:47:23,132
In fact, it's almost brilliant.

629
00:47:24,300 --> 00:47:25,343
Kondo...

630
00:47:30,014 --> 00:47:32,141
Never mind Hijikata's
scribbles

631
00:47:32,975 --> 00:47:34,310
use this one.

632
00:47:36,103 --> 00:47:37,938
Who does he think he is?

633
00:47:38,022 --> 00:47:40,441
Now, now.
Let's see what you've got.

634
00:47:45,279 --> 00:47:46,572
"The Corps Code.

635
00:47:49,825 --> 00:47:53,954
One: Do not stray
from the Way of the samurai.

636
00:47:53,996 --> 00:47:59,085
One: Desertion of the corps
is forbidden.

637
00:47:59,126 --> 00:48:03,047
One: You are forbidden to raise
money without authorization.

638
00:48:03,130 --> 00:48:07,927
One: You are forbidden to
involve yourself in litigation.

639
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:12,640
One: Do not engage
in personal fights.

640
00:48:15,142 --> 00:48:17,186
Any who violate these articles

641
00:48:20,356 --> 00:48:21,524
must commit seppuku."

642
00:48:23,109 --> 00:48:25,277
That's pretty harsh, isn't it?

643
00:48:25,361 --> 00:48:29,532
Okita. This is no time
for such naive talk.

644
00:48:29,615 --> 00:48:32,743
This isn't Shieikan anymore.

645
00:48:32,827 --> 00:48:35,496
To restore order
to the chaos in Kyo

646
00:48:35,538 --> 00:48:38,916
the unity of our corps
is absolutely essential.

647
00:48:38,999 --> 00:48:41,836
[Okita] But still,
seppuku seems extreme.

648
00:48:41,877 --> 00:48:43,379
Yamanami.

649
00:48:44,505 --> 00:48:45,673
[Yamanami]
What is it?

650
00:48:45,756 --> 00:48:47,299
You're against it, too?

651
00:48:48,926 --> 00:48:50,511
Add two more.

652
00:48:58,144 --> 00:48:59,937
One:

653
00:49:00,020 --> 00:49:01,355
Draw your swords and fight
until you strike down

654
00:49:01,439 --> 00:49:04,233
your opponent
or are struck down yourself.

655
00:49:04,316 --> 00:49:05,443
One:

656
00:49:07,027 --> 00:49:08,654
If you fail to kill
and take a wound to your back

657
00:49:08,737 --> 00:49:09,947
it is seppuku.

658
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:12,575
[Okita]
That means...

659
00:49:13,993 --> 00:49:15,744
Once you draw your sword,
you must win.

660
00:49:15,828 --> 00:49:17,037
Soji.

661
00:49:18,706 --> 00:49:20,332
This is about resolve.

662
00:49:23,794 --> 00:49:25,504
Without this level of resolve

663
00:49:28,090 --> 00:49:30,301
you can't protect
the things that matter.

664
00:49:30,384 --> 00:49:32,511
[♪♪♪]

665
00:49:35,890 --> 00:49:37,266
I...

666
00:49:41,228 --> 00:49:43,355
don't want to lose
any more comrades.

667
00:49:47,568 --> 00:49:48,652
[Yamanami]
That's true.

668
00:49:51,280 --> 00:49:54,158
The stricter these rules are

669
00:49:54,241 --> 00:49:57,411
the more justification
we'll have to keep

670
00:49:57,453 --> 00:50:00,080
Serizawa's rogue faction
in check.

671
00:50:00,122 --> 00:50:01,415
[Kondo]
A just cause.

672
00:50:01,499 --> 00:50:03,125
[Yamanami]
Yes.

673
00:50:03,209 --> 00:50:05,461
At the very least,
it should slow them down.

674
00:50:06,921 --> 00:50:09,131
[Oume] Is it good?
[Serizawa] Yes.

675
00:50:09,215 --> 00:50:11,133
[Yamazaki]
The Corps Code?

676
00:50:13,302 --> 00:50:17,890
"One: Do not stray
from the Way of the samurai.

677
00:50:17,973 --> 00:50:21,560
One: Desertion of the corps
is forbidden.

678
00:50:21,602 --> 00:50:23,437
One: You are forbidden to raise
money without authorization."

679
00:50:23,479 --> 00:50:25,105
This is Yamazaki.
He can memorize

680
00:50:25,189 --> 00:50:27,691
anything he sees and hears,
down to every detail

681
00:50:27,775 --> 00:50:30,778
and is able to recall it
perfectly.

682
00:50:30,861 --> 00:50:32,488
[Serizawa]
A natural-born spy, huh?

683
00:50:32,571 --> 00:50:35,032
"One: You are forbidden to
involve yourself in litigation.

684
00:50:35,115 --> 00:50:36,867
Anyone who violates
these rules..."

685
00:50:36,951 --> 00:50:38,619
YAMAZAKI SUSUMU

686
00:50:38,702 --> 00:50:40,079
"Seppuku."

687
00:50:42,456 --> 00:50:44,667
[neck cracking]

688
00:50:44,750 --> 00:50:46,502
Mm-- Mm.

689
00:50:49,338 --> 00:50:51,382
The stricter these rules are

690
00:50:51,465 --> 00:50:53,342
the more justification
we'll have

691
00:50:53,425 --> 00:50:57,596
to keep Serizawa's rogue faction
in check.

692
00:50:57,680 --> 00:51:00,391
This is obviously aimed at us.
A just cause?

693
00:51:00,474 --> 00:51:01,767
Those bastards.

694
00:51:01,850 --> 00:51:03,143
We have to do something.

695
00:51:03,227 --> 00:51:05,312
I like it. The "Corps Code."

696
00:51:05,354 --> 00:51:08,357
What?
But this business

697
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:10,401
about committing seppuku
for breaking them...

698
00:51:10,484 --> 00:51:11,569
I don't like it.

699
00:51:11,652 --> 00:51:13,195
If we play this right,

700
00:51:13,279 --> 00:51:15,990
we could use it
to tighten the noose.

701
00:51:16,031 --> 00:51:17,825
[Serizawa]
Is that so?

702
00:51:17,908 --> 00:51:19,577
[Niimi]
Hey. Good work.

703
00:51:19,660 --> 00:51:22,871
[exclaiming frantically]
Money! Money!

704
00:51:29,461 --> 00:51:30,671
[Serizawa sighs]

705
00:51:33,215 --> 00:51:36,343
[insects chirring]

706
00:51:51,317 --> 00:51:54,486
Half past six. I'll be waiting
at Shinkenji Temple.

707
00:52:02,620 --> 00:52:03,746
Guess who?

708
00:52:03,829 --> 00:52:04,747
[sword slices]

709
00:52:04,830 --> 00:52:06,749
[blood flowing]

710
00:52:06,832 --> 00:52:08,125
[gasps]

711
00:52:11,920 --> 00:52:16,258
[Yoshiaki Dewa's "Chiruran
Shinsengumi Requiem" playing]
